property.name: text
property.value: This model, whose structure is due to Kahn and MacQueen, calculates integers whose prime factors are only 2, 3, and 5, with no redundancies. It uses the OrderedMerge actor, which takes two monotonically increasing input sequences and merges them into one monotonically increasing output sequence.

property.name: text
property.value: The output is an ordered sequence of integers of the form 2^n * 3^m * 5^k, where n, m and k are non-negative integers.
